        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 20 at 5:22PM MDT until July 20 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southwestern Prairie County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 615 PM MDT.

* At 521 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 24 miles east of
Hillside, or 27 miles west of Terry, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Terry, Zero, Mccloud, and Calypso.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
